A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 County Boards of Education – Root Causes of Chronic Absenteeism and
3 Expulsion – Investigation and Reporting
4 FOR the purpose of requiring each county board of education to investigate, identify, and
5 report on root causes of chronic absenteeism and expulsion in the county; and
6 generally relating to the investigation and reporting of chronic absenteeism and
7 expulsion.
8 BY adding to
9 Article – Education
10 Section 4–147
11 Annotated Code of Maryland
12 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
13 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
14 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
15 Article – Education
16 4–147.
17 (A) EACH COUNTY BOARD SHALL INVESTIGATE AND IDENTIFY ROOT
18 CAUSES OF CHRONIC ABSENTEEISM AND EXPULSION IN THE COUNTY.
19 (B) (1) AN INVESTIGATION PERFORMED UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS
20 SECTION SHALL EXAMINE A STUDENT’S:
21 (I) DOMESTIC SITUATION;
