1 (II) FAMILY VACATIONS;
2 (III) HISTORY OF ALCOHOL OR DRUG ADDICTION;
3 (IV) MENTAL HEALTH;
4 (V) PHYSICAL HEALTH; AND
5 (VI) SCHOOL ENVIRONMENT.
6 (2) THE INVESTIGATION SHALL ALSO EXAMINE WHETHER THE
7 STUDENT IS PROVIDING:
8 (I) CARE FOR SOMEONE IN THE STUDENT’S HOUSEHOLD; OR
9 (II) LANGUAGE TRANSLATION FOR A MEMBER OF THE
10 STUDENT’S HOUSEHOLD WHO IS SICK.
11 (C) BEGINNING JANUARY 1, 2026, AND EACH QUARTER THEREAFTER FOR A
12 PERIOD OF 10 YEARS, EACH COUNTY BOARD SHALL REPORT, IN ACCORDANCE WITH
13 § 2–1257 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE, TO EACH APPLICABLE COUNTY
14 DELEGATION TO THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY, THE SENATE EDUCATION, ENERGY, AND
15 THE ENVIRONMENT COMMITTEE, AND THE HOUSE WAYS AND MEANS COMMITTEE,
16 ON THE FINDINGS UNDER SUBSECTION (B) OF THIS SECTION.
17 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
18 1, 2025.

